- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with error correction codes and derives bounds on their cardinality using sphere packing arguments.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the construction of codes for correcting tandem duplication errors.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper may involve parallel processing techniques for error correction.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper may involve the study of error correction in networked systems.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper may involve the analysis of the computational complexity of error correction algorithms.
